          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Frame inconsistency arises from independent per-frame denoising, high CFG amplification of errors, and the absence of an explicit 3-D scene state."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Temporal attention (AnimateDiff-style) is the dominant architectural fix: a motion module inserted into a frozen SD U-Net learns frame correlations from video data without disturbing image priors."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Shared noise initialisation (alpha-blended) is a zero-cost inference trick that substantially reduces low-frequency flicker."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "CLIP Temporal Consistency (mean adjacent-frame cosine sim) is the standard fast metric; real videos score ≈ 0.985 and good models score ≈ 0.975–0.982."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Long videos require overlapping sliding windows with context seeding — without it, consecutive generated segments are visually unrelated."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Video DiTs with 3-D VAE (CogVideoX) achieve the highest consistency end-to-end at the cost of much larger compute budgets."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
